parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not be adequately protected.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the vehicle is involved in a crash and the airbag does not deploy
the driver and passengers are injured or killed in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries or distractions to the driver, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: the airbag deploys while the vehicle is in motion
the driver is injured by the deploying airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing or replacing the Takata airbag can leave drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The driver receives a recall notice but the parts are not available
the dealer confirms that the parts are not available
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the ignition switch feels loose or worn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked exhaust manifold can cause carbon monoxide to leak into the vehicle's cabin, posing a serious health risk to occupants. It can also cause the check engine light to come on and lead to engine performance issues.
A faulty oxygen sensor can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to engine performance issues and decreased fuel efficiency.
A faulty distributor can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
A faulty ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or slip while shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: the transmission makes a loud noise
or the vehicle shakes while shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or slip while shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
or the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: the ignition switch has to be turned multiple times to start the vehicle
or the vehicle stalls while driving.
